Level 1 
Means an Employee who has performed as an Entry Level employee for the previous 12 
months (or 1976 hours, whichever occurs later) and been assessed by the Employer as 
being competent at all function of the Level 1 and who is required to perform, and does 
perform, any or all of the following functions or is required to operate and does operate, the 
following equipment, and who has completed all appropriate licences, and who has been 
assessed by the Employer as being competent to a high level in those functions or 
equipment: 

• Subject to close supervision by higher level employees; 
• Responsible for the setup of equipment, ensuring all equipment is appropriate 

and operational for the assigned task; 
• Responsible for the setup of suitable lighting and adjusts appropriately; 
• Setup of appropriate computer equipment; 
• Setup and use of online ordering system; 
• Take customer orders for videos or photos; 
• Assist customers with the operation of the  automated  ordering

