DC Team 
Member  
Grade A  



Inventory team member - Experience: 
An Inventory team member is an experienced team member who specialises in managing, 
investigating and resolving inventory tasks, they are responsible for the following specialised and 
complexed inventory operational tasks including but not limited to: 
➢ slotting management, including requests to WMS teams for slotting changes; 
➢ slotting management, including approved and allocated areas in WCS (Warehouse Control 

System – OSR  Automation ); 
➢ inventory accuracy practices include cycle counts, investigations and system reconciliations; 
➢ performing tasks as part of execution of inventory programs; 
➢ supporting product access controls (locked/unlocked stock); 
➢ undertaking audits and completing investigations to inventory; 
➢ complete controls to resolve inventory issues, including escalations;  
➢ data management for inventory control purposes.
